content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 17 ยง 8119.00 - General

State Regulations
(a) [Eff. until

Sept. 1, 1999, see also subd. (a) below.] Route 23. Route 23 between the Greene/Columbia county line and Route 32
in the Village of Catskill and the Towns of Cairo and Catskill. (a) [Eff. Sept. 1, 1999, see also subd. (a) above.] Route 23. Route 23 from
the Delaware/Greene county line to the Greene/Columbia county line in the

Village of Catskill and the Towns of Catskill, Cairo, Durham, Windham, Ashland
and Prattsville. (b) [Eff. until

July 11, 2001, see also subd. (b) below.] US Route 9W. US Route 9W between the

Albany/Greene county line and the Route 81/Route 385 intersection in the Towns
of New Baltimore and Coxsackie. (b) [Eff. July 11, 2001, see also subd. (b) above.] US Route 9W. US Route 9W
between the Greene-Albany county line and CR 9 in the Towns of New Baltimore
and Coxsackie, a distance of 3.3+- miles. (c) Route 32. Route 32 between the

Albany/Greene county line and the Route 23/Route 32 overlap in the Towns of

Cairo and Greenville. (d) Route 81. Route 81 between the Albany/Greene county line and Route 32 in the Towns of

Greenville and Durham. Notes
